         <abstract>
            <p>We examine the integers $V(n, k)$ defined by means of $$k! \sum_{n=0}^\infty V(n, k)x^n/n! = \lbrack x(e^x + 1) - 2(e^x - 1) \rbrack^k,$$ and, in particular, we show how these integers are related to the Bernoulli, Genocchi and van der Pol numbers, and the numbers generated by the reciprocal of $e^x - x - 1$. We prove that the $V(n, k)$ are also related to the numbers $W(n, k)$ defined by $$k! \sum_{n=0}^\infty W(n, k)x^n/n! = \lbrack (x - 2)(e^x - 1) \rbrack^k$$ in much the same way the associated Stirling numbers are related to the Stirling numbers. Finally, we examine, more generally, the Bell polynomials $B_{n,k}(a_1, a_2, 3 - \alpha, 4 - \alpha, 5 - \alpha,\ldots)$ and show how the methods of this paper can be used to prove several formulas involving the Bernoulli and Stirling numbers.</p>
          </abstract>
